 General Hand Detection and Pose Challenge<body>            	 	    General Hand Detection and Pose Challenge  	   	                                      	 	   	     	       		 		    			      Contents  		   		   			         Contents    		         		      Introduction    		          Data Formats    		          Camera Intrinsics    		          			  Index of Sequences    		          Test			  Sequences    		          Other Datasets    		      		 	       	       	      		  		    Introduction   		 		   		 		  Dear Colleague,		  		   		    Here we introduce the General-HANDS data-set. Our		    objective is to provide a standard		    dataset on which to evaluate hand detection &amp; pose estimation		    systems. The dataset aims to encompass a complete variety of		    sequences, demonstrating different view-points,		    scales, poses, occlusions, and camera		    technologies. We have captured  22 		    of our own sequences and welcome outside		    contributions. 		   		   		    We are happy to run your code on these		    sequences if you will provide us an implementation (in		    either executable or source form). Otherwise,		    We supplicate you to submit results on any of the		    following challenges for 		    whichever subset of the sequences you feel to		    be appropriate for your algorithm (to		    jsupanci@uci.edu). 		   		    		      Hand Detection: for each image produce a file		      containing one line per detection (eg output_$ID.txt). Each line		      should contain 4 numbers indicating the center		      of the hand: x, y (in pixels), z (in cm) and a confidence.		     		     		      Hand Key-point localization: as above, but		      additionally append an x,y,z,r value for each		      key point to the detection line. The key-points are as		      follows (Common		      Name/  libhand   name/Abbreviation: 		         pinky-tip / NA / F11   			  pinky-knuckle / finger1joint3 / F13  			  pinky-base / finger1joint1 / F4  			  ring-tip / NA / F21  			  ring-knuckle / finger2joint3 / F23  			  ring-base / finger2joint1 / F24   			  middle-tip / NA / F31  			  middle-knuckle / finger3joint3 / F33 			  middle-base / finger3joint1 / F34  			  index-tip / NA / F41  			  index-knuckle / finger4joint3 / F43  			  index-base / finger4joint1 / F44   			  thumb-tip / NA / F51  			  thumb-knuckle / finger5joint3 / F52  			  thumb-base / finger5joint2 / F53  			  palm-center / Bone / P2  			  wrist / Metacarpals / P1  		        			To clarify the format, we give several ground			truth annotations (click on the image for the			expected output). 		       		       			 			    			 			    			 			    		       		     		     		      Semantic Segmentation. For each image, produce		      an RGB image with the following semantic		      segmentation.		       			  		     		     Kind Regards		 	       	       		 		    			      Index of Sequences  		   		   		  		       Sequence Title 			 Camera Type 			 Sign Language 			 Gestures 			 Activities &amp; Objects 			 Egocentric Activities 			 Supervisory Viewpoints 		          			    			     HCI_FAR0 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 yes 			 no 			 no 			 no 		          			    			     HCI_FAR1 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 yes 			 yes 			 no 			 no 		          			    			     HCI_FAR2 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 yes 			 no 			 no 			 no 		          			    			     HCI_FAR3 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 yes 			 no 			 no 			 no 		          			    			     HCI_FAR4 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 yes 			 no 			 no 			 no 		          			    			     HCI_FAR5 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 yes 			 no 			 no 			 no 		          			    			     HCI_FAR6 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 yes 			 yes 			 no 			 no 		          			    			     HCI_ABOVE0 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 yes 			 yes 			 no 			 yes 		          			    			     OCCLUSION0 ASUS/Xtion 			   			  			 ASUS/Xtion 			 no 			 